org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the Court of the United States for the District of Washington
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Application of Rudolf Tschable, for a writ of habeas corpus.

This matter coming on regularly to be heard on the application of the above named complainant for a writ of habeas corpus and upon an order to show cause why such writ of habeas corpus should not be issued, the complainant being represented by his attorney Ralph S.Pierce and the Secretary of Labor of the United States and the Commissioner of Immigration, Henry M.White, being represented by Ben L.Moore, Assistant United States District Attorney, and a return to said writ having been duly and regularly made, and the matter having been fully presented to the court by counsel, and the court being fully advised in the premises,
NOW THEREFORE, IT IS ORDERED ADJUDGED AND DECREED that the application of the complaint for a writ of habeas corpus be, and that the same is hereby granted, and

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED,ADJUDGED AND DECREED that the complainant be forthwith discharged from the custody of the said Henry M.White as Commissioner of Labor of the United States unless the District Atorney of the United States shall request that he be further held.
Done in open court this 4th day of January, 1919.
